                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1947v07</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d634</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">634</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1947-03-28T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1947-03-28T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="634" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d634">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.248/3–2847</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Secretary of War</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Patterson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-28">March 28,
                            1947</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Before Secretary Marshall left
                    for Moscow he indicated that he attached great importance to the rapid
                    completion of the civilian end-use portion of the 8⅓ Group Chinese Air Force
                    Program. I would like to make clear that the statement in my letter of March 6,
                        1947,<note n="58" xml:id="d634fn1">Not printed.</note> that first priority
                    for transferable military equipment should be assigned to Greece, was not
                    intended to mean that any action should be taken which would delay the
                    completion of this Chinese program.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dean Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
